
# 💳 Credit Card Fraud Detection (End-to-End ML Pipeline)

## 📌 Overview

This project builds an end-to-end machine learning pipeline to detect fraudulent credit card transactions using a highly imbalanced dataset.

The goal is to simulate a **real-world fraud detection system**, covering:

* Data preprocessing
* Model training and evaluation
* Model persistence
* Inference pipeline (deployment-style predictions)

---

## 🚀 Project Structure

```
📁 fraud-detection/
│
├── 01-card-fraud-dection-data-preparation.ipynb
├── 02-card-fraud-dection-model-training.ipynb
├── 03-card-fraud-dection-prediction.ipynb
│
├── artifacts/
│   ├── fraud_nn_model.keras
│   ├── scaler.pkl
│   ├── feature_names.pkl
│
└── README.md
```

---

## 📊 Dataset

* Source: ULB Machine Learning Group
* https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mlg-ulb/creditcardfraud
* Contains anonymized credit card transactions
* Highly imbalanced:

  * ~99.8% normal transactions
  * ~0.2% fraud cases

---

## ⚙️ Workflow

### 1️⃣ Data Preparation

* Load dataset
* Handle missing values
* Feature selection
* Train/test split
* Save datasets as `.npy` for reuse

---

### 2️⃣ Model Training

* Models explored:

  * Linear Regression
  * Random Forest
  * Neural Network (Keras)

* Techniques used:

  * Standardization (Scaler)
  * Threshold tuning (critical for fraud detection)
  * Evaluation using:

    * Confusion Matrix
    * Precision / Recall / F1-score

* Key challenge:

  * **Imbalanced data → focus on recall vs precision tradeoff**

---

### 3️⃣ Inference Pipeline

Simulates real-world deployment:

* Load saved artifacts:

  * trained model
  * scaler
  * feature list
* Accept new transaction data
* Apply preprocessing
* Generate fraud probability
* Apply decision threshold

---

## 🧠 Key Learnings

* In fraud detection:

  * **Recall is often more important than accuracy**
  * Missing fraud = financial loss

* Threshold tuning is critical:

  * Default 0.5 is not optimal for imbalanced datasets

* Separation of training and inference is essential for:

  * reproducibility
  * production readiness

---

## 📈 Example Results

| Metric    | Value                        |
| --------- | ---------------------------- |
| Accuracy  | ~99%                         |
| Precision | High                         |
| Recall    | Tuned (trade-off controlled) |

> Note: Performance depends heavily on threshold selection.

